column1: University of Birmingham Positron Imaging Centre
This is a sample of an experiment run at the Univesity of Birmingham. It
consists of a single 1 mm diameter MCC particle activated with Fluorine-18
radioactive tracer material inside a bubbling fluidised bed. The fluidised bed
was filled with 90% sand and 10% MCC; air was fed into the bottom of the bed at
a rate of 37 litres per minute at 3.5 bar.
Columns are formatted as [t, x1, y1, x2, y2], where the `t` represents the LoR
timestamp (ms), x1 and y1 represent the LoR coordinates on the first detector
screen (mm), and x2 and y2 represent the LoR coordinates on the second screen.
